<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Betula</i> <i>glandulosa</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>tridentata</i> ssp. <i>vaseyana</i>, <i>Ribes</i> <i>inerme</i>, <i>Salix</i> <i>bebbiana</i>, <i>Salix</i> <i>boothii</i>, <i>Salix</i> <i>eastwoodiae</i> and <i>Salix</i> <i>lucida</i>. Emergent conifers may be present at low cover, including <i>Abies</i> <i>concolor</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 4 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Montane perennially wet meadows, stream sides. Soils are alluvial and usually deep with an organic layer.  </div>
</div>

		
